com.scvngr.levelup.deeplinkauth

Class DeepLinkAuthUtil

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.scvngr.levelup.deeplinkauth.DeepLinkAuthUtil

  • public final class DeepLinkAuthUtil
extends Object
    Utilities to support deep link authorization. This class is not intended to be used directly by 3rd party apps for integration; instead please see LevelUpDeepLinkIntegrator.

        See Also:
        getPackageSignature(android.content.Context, String)

      • getPackageSignature

        public static String getPackageSignature(Context context,
                         String packageName)
                                  throws IllegalArgumentException
        Given a package, retrieves the Google Maps-style API key signature. This is in the form of SIGNATURE;PACKAGE where SIGNATURE is the signature of the package, in upper case hexadecimal characters, grouped in bytes by ":". PACKAGE is the provided package name.
        Parameters:
        context - an Application context.
        packageName - the name of the package.
        Returns:
        the package's signature.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the provided package has no signatures or is otherwise unusable.

      • isLevelUpAvailable

        public static boolean isLevelUpAvailable(Context context)
        Parameters:
        context - application context.
        Returns:
        true if a version of LevelUp that supports deep link authorization is installed and available.

      • getRequestPermissionsIntent

        public static Intent getRequestPermissionsIntent(Context context,
                                 int appId,
                                 Collection<String> permissions)
                                          throws DeepLinkAuthUtil.LevelUpNotInstalledException
        Makes a request for permissions, verifying that the target of the Intent is authentically LevelUp.
        Parameters:
        context - application context.
        appId - the web service ID of the app requesting the permissions.
        permissions - the set of permissions.
        Returns:
        an intent intended to be sent with startActivityForResult().
        Throws:
        DeepLinkAuthUtil.LevelUpNotInstalledException - if LevelUp is not installed.
